{
  "name": "Scorch Release Majestic Violent Murdering Hellfire Destroyer",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Shakuton.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You conjure an innumerable number of globes of superheated flame, fusing them, to create a single massive sphere of super-heated flame.</p><p>Make a ranged ninjutsu attack against a target you can see within range, dealing 8d12+8 Fire damage on a hit.</p><p>Regardless if you hit or miss, all other creatures within 60 feet of the original target must succeed a Constitution Saving Throw taking 3d12+3 Fire damage and being Burned on a failed save.</p><p>Creatures who's hit points are reduced to 0 as a result of this jutsu are turned to dust and leave behind only a shadow of their physique stained in ash on the ground or wall.</p><p>You can spend motes created by the Scorch Release: Scorching Murder to enhance this jutsu. For every mote spent, increase both instances of damage by 1d12+1. You can spend up to 6 motes this way.</p>",
